{"title":"School Governance (Constitution) Regulations 2012","public_updated_at":"2012-10-24T09:00:00Z","details":{"body":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>This statutory guidance is for:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>school leaders</li>\n  <li>school staff</li>\n  <li>governing bodies</li>\n  <li>local authorities</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>It explains the arrangements for the constitution of governing bodies of all maintained schools:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>formed on or after 1 September 2012</li>\n  <li>or whose instrument of government has been changed on or after 1 September 2012</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>The guidance covers:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>the description of the different categories of governor</li>\n  <li>how governing bodies are to be constituted</li>\n  <li>terms of office</li>\n  <li>removal and disqualification of governors</li>\n  <li>instruments of government</li>\n  <li>all aspects of the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.legislation.gov.uk/uksi/2012/1034/contents/made\">School Governance (Constitution) (England) Regulations 2012</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>The guidance contains a table showing the constitution of governing bodies by category of governor (annex A).</p>\n\n<p>There is also a model instrument of government (annex B) which is also available separately for schools to download and fill in.</p>\n\n<p>The <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.legislation.gov.uk/uksi/2007/957/contents/made\">School Governance (Constitution) (England) Regulations 2007</a> continue to apply to existing governing bodies until they decide to make a change to their instrument of government.</p>\n\n<p>Schools where this is the case should refer to the statutory guidance on the ‘<a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/school-governance-constitution-regulations-2007\">School Governance (Constitution) Regulations 2007</a>’ instead.</p>\n\n</div>","change_history":[{"public_timestamp":"2012-10-24T10:00:00.000+01:00","note":"First published."}],"documents":["<section class=\"attachment embed